    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>BIG AIRBUS ORDER</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By John Tagliabue</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Tagliabue, John</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Airbus Industrie books order for up to 50 aircraft with list price of more than $3 billion from International Lease Finance Corp, unit of American International Group (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The European aircraft consortium, Airbus Industrie, booked an order for up to 50 aircraft with a list price of more than $3 billion from the International Lease Finance Corporation of Los Angeles, a unit of American International Group. Last year, Airbus led its American rival, Boeing, in orders, by 476 to 391, but their order backlogs are about equal at 1,600 each.</p>
        <p>John Tagliabue (NYT)</p>
      </block>
